===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|egremoyne}}, from a conflation of {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|agrimonia}} and {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|agremoine}} (from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|agremoine}}, variant of {{m|fro|aegremone}}), both from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|agrimōnia}}, metathesized from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|argemōnia||a kind of poppy}} (probably by association with {{m|la|ager|ager, agri-|field}}), from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ἀργεμώνη||{{w|Papaver argemone}}, wild-rose}}, probably from {{m|grc|ἄργεμον||[[leucoma]]}}, from {{m|grc|ἀργός||white}}.

